  "body": "Have not measured it in detail, nor investigated the assembly, but possibly a variant of this (with a new error type) _might_ shave off some cycles\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/core/vm/interpreter.go b/core/vm/interpreter.go\r\nindex 673f046a46..7609ab3be2 100644\r\n--- a/core/vm/interpreter.go\r\n+++ b/core/vm/interpreter.go\r\n@@ -188,10 +188,8 @@ func (in *EVMInterpreter) Run(contract *Contract, input []byte, readOnly bool) (\r\n \t\top = contract.GetOp(pc)\r\n \t\toperation := in.cfg.JumpTable[op]\r\n \t\t// Validate stack\r\n-\t\tif sLen := stack.len(); sLen < operation.minStack {\r\n-\t\t\treturn nil, &ErrStackUnderflow{stackLen: sLen, required: operation.minStack}\r\n-\t\t} else if sLen > operation.maxStack {\r\n-\t\t\treturn nil, &ErrStackOverflow{stackLen: sLen, limit: operation.maxStack}\r\n+\t\tif !stack.between(operation.minStack, operation.maxStack) {\r\n+\t\t\treturn nil, ErrOutOfGas\r\n \t\t}\r\n \t\t// Static portion of gas\r\n \t\tcost = operation.constantGas // For tracing\r\ndiff --git a/core/vm/stack.go b/core/vm/stack.go\r\nindex 9e7e887ccd..e891c17a74 100644\r\n--- a/core/vm/stack.go\r\n+++ b/core/vm/stack.go\r\n@@ -65,6 +65,10 @@ func (st *Stack) len() int {\r\n \treturn len(st.data)\r\n }\r\n \r\n+func (st *Stack) between(low, high int) bool {\r\n+\treturn len(st.data) > low && len(st.data) < high\r\n+}\r\n+\r\n func (st *Stack) swap(n int) {\r\n \tst.data[st.len()-n], st.data[st.len()-1] = st.data[st.len()-1], st.data[st.len()-n]\r\n }\r\n```",
