    "body": "We will check it out.\r\n\r\nFrom my experimentation in evmone:\r\n1. For stack overflow check you only need one bit of information: \"may overflow stack\". This is because all instructions at most increase the stack height by 1.\r\n2. I also check the stack height itself fist: `len(st.data) == 1024 && operation.mayOverflow`.\r\n3. And the stack underflow is only checked if `len(st.data) != 1024`.",
